    <div class="header">
      <h1>Android Smoke Tracker</h1>
      <h2><a href="http://dhappy.org">Will Holcomb</a></h2>
      <h2>4 September 2013</h2>
    </div>

    <p>I'm interested in tracking my behavior over time to help get a better sense of them. I've been using <a href="//play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=uk.amimetic.faillog">Fail Log</a> to keep track of my smoking habit. I like the app for a couple reasons:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>It includes a widget that allows logging an event with two clicks</li>
      <li>There is rudimentary data analytics which include a heatmap showing usage through the week and a breakdown according to times</li>
      <li>The list of activities is extensible</li>
    </ul>

    <p>The app is less than ideal in that:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>All "failures" are lumped together for analytics purposes</li>
      <li>Data is available only on the phone; no syncing with the internet</li>
      <li>The analytics are largely textual</li>
      <li>I'd like the name to be a bit more ambiguous. I'm looking to collect data to analyze and don't want to be so judgemental about it.</li>
      <li>
        My ideal application would conglomerate data from bunches of users and give me a display that says things like:
        <ul>
          <li>here are your likely health outcomes from smoking now</li>
          <li>here are your outcomes if you wait 15 minutes</li>
          <li>your ideal wait time given your past performance is <em>x</em> minutes</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p>I'd like an application that provides a web interface for analyzing the data with more graphical elements. This blog post will cover the creation of such an application.</p>

    <p>I'll be developing using <a href="//eclipse.org/">Eclipse</a>. To start out:</p>

    <ol>
      <li>Download the code from <a href="">github</a></li>
      <li>In Eclipse: <code>File</code> &rarr; <code>Import</code></li>
      <li>For import source use: <code>Android</code> &rarr; <code>Existing Android Code Into Workspace</code></li>
    </ol>

    <p>The basic workflow follows Fail Log:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>
        A screen to list all habits
        <ul>
          <li>clicking on one saves a new instance</li>
          <li>long pressing one brings up a menu allowing: listing of all instances, deleting</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        A list of instances
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p>Storing the data requires two tables:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>
        habits
        <ul>
          <li>int id</li>
          <li>string name</li>
          <li>string description</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        habits
        <ul>
          <li>int id</li>
          <li>int habit_id</li>
          <li>int time</li>
          <li>string description</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>

